cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning, which are both subfields of computer science. The use of deep learning models and word vectors suggests that it belongs to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of bag-of-words model suggests that it may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of character-enhanced word vectors suggests that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
